This paper discusses the use of a semantic wiki and controlled natural language for ontology creation and modification, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), databases (cs.DB), information retrieval (cs.IR), and software engineering (cs.SE). The use of natural language processing and semantic technologies suggests a focus on AI and CL, while the use of a wiki platform and database integration suggests a focus on DB and SE. The paper's emphasis on ontology creation and modification suggests a focus on IR as well.
